, `/.gitignore` (entries: `packages/app-desktop/ElectronAppWrapper.test.js`)|Added ignore entries for the generated test artifact file to prevent linting/tracking of the transpiled test output.|\n\n## Suggested labels\n\nbug, desktop\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>🚥 Pre-merge checks | ✅ 6</summary>\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ Passed checks (6 passed)</summary>\n\n|               Check name              | Status   | Explanation                                                                                                                                                                                             |\n| :-----------------------------------: | :------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n|              Title check              | ✅ Passed | The title accurately describes the main fix: preventing a TypeError in handleAppFailure when the window is destroyed, directly addressing issue `#14687`.                                                 |\n|           Description check           | ✅ Passed | The description clearly relates to the changeset, detailing the problem, solution, and testing approach for the window destruction race condition fix.                                                  |\n|          Linked Issues check          | ✅ Passed | The code changes fully address issue `#14687` by implementing defensive guard clauses using isDestroyed() at both entry and restart points, preventing TypeError when accessing destroyed window objects. |\n|       Out of Scope Changes check      | ✅ Passed | All changes are scoped to fixing the race condition: ElectronAppWrapper.ts guards, test file addition, and configuration file updates (.eslintignore, .gitignore) for the new test.                     |\n|           Do